external_knowledge:
dudes = male users;
land of the free and the home of the brave = United States;
happiness level = satisfaction rate;

sql:
SELECT AVG(annual_income) AS average_annual_income
FROM users
WHERE satisfaction_rate > 8 AND number_of_languages_spoken > 1;

SELECT name, satisfaction_rate 
FROM users 
ORDER BY satisfaction_rate DESC;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM user_feedback
WHERE feedback_date BETWEEN DATE('now', '-30 days') AND DATE('now');

external_knowledge:
- "affluent yet discontented crew" refers to users with an annual income over $50,000 and a satisfaction rate below the average;
- "linguistic abilities" refer to the languages the users speak;
- "sailing below the average satisfaction level" means having a satisfaction rate lower than the average satisfaction rate of all users.

Happiness levels refer to the satisfaction rates provided by users; groups of people refer to user segments; sharing thoughts refers to submitting feedback once or more.;
The happiness level is measured on a scale from 1 to 10.;
People who have not shared their thoughts are not considered in the analysis.

sql:
SELECT name, email
FROM users
WHERE satisfaction_rate < (SELECT AVG(feedback_rating) FROM user_feedback);
